      "message": "Line 42: 🟡 Suggestion: `isCallNotification` now uses `originalPriority`, so call pushes that FCM actually delivered as normal priority will still acquire a wakelock, attempt to start a foreground service, and trigger `connectivityChanged(true)`. That bypasses the previous delivered-priority guard and can reintroduce background wakeups for messages FCM intentionally downgraded. Prefer keeping `remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH` for runtime behavior, or split the checks so only the call-type filtering changes the connectivity path. Suggested fix:\\n```suggestion\\nval isCallNotification \u003d (pushType.contains(\"audioCall\")\\n        || pushType.contains(\"videoCall\"))\\n        \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\\n```",
